{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1769622663,"nonce":"FNy3pXkC8dwmdkEvPoVNxHgfdug=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87meBCtzwAAAAU0WVvk"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1770131061,"nonce":"zJ+tG/4SKyypzGckDWThV3/zANA=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87k_maI","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/103#issuecomment-3841877640"},"message":"## Enforcement Gap: Worktree Usage Not Enforced\n\n**Observed Violation**: During work on issue #130, I attempted to create a feature branch directly in the main workspace using `git checkout -b feature/issue-130-git-editor-fix` instead of using the required worktree workflow. The user had to intervene and remind me to use `worktree_create.sh`.\n\n**Current State**: Issue #103 proposes blocking commits to `main`, but doesn't prevent agents from:\n- Creating feature branches in the main workspace tree\n- Working directly in `/ros2_agent_workspace` instead of `/.workspace-worktrees/`\n\n**The Problem**: AI_RULES.md is explicit:\n\u003e **⚠️ CRITICAL: All agents MUST use isolated worktrees for task work.**\n\u003e **🚫 Forbidden**: Direct `git checkout -b` or working in main workspace tree\n\nBut there's no **technical enforcement** to prevent this violation.\n\n## Proposed Additional Enforcement\n\n### 1. Git Branch Creation Hook\n\nCreate a wrapper or hook that blocks feature branch creation in main workspace:\n\n```bash\n# .agent/scripts/enforce-worktree.sh\n# Source this in env.sh or use as git alias\n\nif command -v git \u0026\u003e /dev/null; then\n  git() {\n    # Intercept 'git checkout -b' in main workspace\n    if [[ \"$1\" == \"checkout\" ]] \u0026\u0026 [[ \"$2\" == \"-b\" ]]; then\n      # Check if we're in main workspace (not a worktree)\n      if [[ \"$PWD\" == */ros2_agent_workspace ]] \u0026\u0026 [[ \"$PWD\" != */.workspace-worktrees/* ]] \u0026\u0026 [[ \"$PWD\" != */.layer-worktrees/* ]]; then\n        echo \"❌ ERROR: Don't create feature branches in main workspace!\"\n        echo \"\"\n        echo \"✅ Required workflow:\"\n        echo \"   .agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue \u003cN\u003e --type workspace\"\n        echo \"   source .agent/scripts/worktree_enter.sh --issue \u003cN\u003e\"\n        echo \"\"\n        echo \"See: .agent/AI_RULES.md - Standard Workflow (Step 4)\"\n        return 1\n      fi\n    fi\n    \n    # Pass through to real git\n    command git \"$@\"\n  }\nfi\n```\n\n### 2. Enhanced Status Check\n\nUpdate `status_report.sh` to warn if agent is in main workspace:\n\n```bash\n# Detect if in main workspace (risky for task work)\nif [[ \"$PWD\" == */ros2_agent_workspace ]] \u0026\u0026 [[ \"$PWD\" != */.workspace-worktrees/* ]]; then\n  echo \"⚠️  WARNING: You are in the main workspace.\"\n  echo \"   For task work, use: .agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh\"\nfi\n```\n\n### 3. Update AI_RULES.md Checklist\n\nMake the worktree requirement more prominent in the \"Before Starting Work\" checklist:\n\n```markdown\n## Before Starting ANY Work\n- [ ] Check GitHub issues for existing work\n- [ ] Verify git identity is configured\n- [ ] **✅ CREATE WORKTREE (never work in main tree)**: `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue \u003cN\u003e --type \u003cworkspace|layer\u003e`\n- [ ] Check current branch (should NOT be main)\n- [ ] Create/assign issue if needed\n```\n\n## Impact\n\nWithout enforcement, agents will continue to violate the worktree protocol despite clear documentation. This leads to:\n- Workspace pollution\n- Merge conflicts between parallel agents\n- Build artifact contamination\n- Harder cleanup when work is abandoned\n\n## Priority\n\n**High** - This violation just occurred despite clear documentation. Technical enforcement is the only reliable solution.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Sonnet 4.5`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1771261452,"nonce":"S+dsSN1JVMZ/IcHumCvflNQK4Tg=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87pB60-","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/103#issuecomment-3909594430"},"message":"## Closing — Core Enforcement Is In Place\n\nThe critical safety enforcement items from this issue have been implemented:\n\n1. **Pre-commit hook blocks commits to `main`** — `no-commit-to-branch` hook in `.pre-commit-config.yaml` blocks commits to `main`, `jazzy`, and `rolling`.\n2. **`git checkout \u003cbranch\u003e` blocked** — `env.sh` wraps `git` and rejects branch-switching checkout while still allowing file-restore forms (`git checkout -- \u003cfile\u003e`).\n3. **Commit identity validation** — `check-commit-identity.py` hook blocks commits from unrecognized identities.\n4. **GitHub issue template** — `feature_track.md` template exists.\n\nThe remaining UX improvements (agent checklist, `make start-issue`, additional issue templates, main-workspace warning in status report) are tracked in a follow-up issue.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1771261452,"nonce":"4AhefGoxGb+pUaQto4vSRs4JiRM=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87meBCtzwAAAAVQ1Qr9"},"status":2}]}